data.description: Make sure not to miss this incredible single-family home situated in the sought-after Upper La Quinta Cove, just a two short blocks from the popular Bear Creek trail, and minutes from the trending shops and restaurants of Old Town La Quinta.Take in the beautiful vistas this home has to offer with approximately 1,434 square feet of living space, this residence offers three bedrooms, two bathrooms, a separate living room featuring a grand rock-faced fireplace, a dining area conveniently adjacent to the kitchen with a sliding glass door opening to the rear patio/yard, and a well-equipped kitchen with an eating bar and direct access to the garage.The master suite is a standout feature, boasting dual wardrobe closets and a private bath with a direct entry to the rear yard. The exterior of the property is designed for low maintenance, including artificial grass in the backyard. Other notable amenities encompass a tile roof, an attached 2-car garage with an automatic door opener, large ceramic tile flooring in all high-traffic areas such as the dining room, kitchen, and bathrooms, indoor laundry facilities, and a brand new AC installed in 2021, and a host of other features to discover.Visit the nearby Fritz Burns Park with 8 Pickleball courts and 6 Tennis courts.Disclosure: Seller is a Licensed Real Estate Agent
